 {"id":"coding_agent_session_search-q14z","title":"P3.5a: Virtual Scrolling for Large Result Sets","description":"# P3.5a: Virtual Scrolling for Large Result Sets

## Goal
Implement efficient virtual scrolling that renders only visible items, enabling smooth navigation through 10K+ search results and long conversations without memory exhaustion or UI lag.

## Why This Task is Critical

The plan specifies NFR-2: <100ms search latency with 100K+ messages. Without virtual scrolling:
- 10K DOM nodes = ~500MB memory, 2s+ render time
- Scrolling becomes janky at 1K+ items
- Mobile devices crash or freeze

Virtual scrolling keeps DOM nodes at O(viewport) instead of O(total).

## Technical Implementation

### Virtual List Component

```javascript
// web/src/components/VirtualList.js

export class VirtualList {
    constructor({
        container,
        itemHeight,
        totalCount,
        renderItem,
        overscan = 3,
        onScrollEnd = null
    }) {
        this.container = container;
        this.itemHeight = itemHeight;
        this.totalCount = totalCount;
        this.renderItem = renderItem;
        this.overscan = overscan;
        this.onScrollEnd = onScrollEnd;

        this.scrollTop = 0;
        this.containerHeight = 0;
        this.items = new Map(); // index -> element

        this.init();
    }

    init() {
        // Create inner container for total height
        this.inner = document.createElement("div");
        this.inner.style.height = `${this.totalCount * this.itemHeight}px`;
        this.inner.style.position = "relative";
        this.container.appendChild(this.inner);

        // Observe container size
        this.resizeObserver = new ResizeObserver(() => this.onResize());
        this.resizeObserver.observe(this.container);

        // Handle scroll
        this.container.addEventListener("scroll", () => this.onScroll(), { passive: true });

        this.render();
    }

    onResize() {
        this.containerHeight = this.container.clientHeight;
        this.render();
    }

    onScroll() {
        this.scrollTop = this.container.scrollTop;
        this.render();

        // Infinite scroll callback
        if (this.onScrollEnd && this.isNearEnd()) {
            this.onScrollEnd();
        }
    }

    isNearEnd() {
        const remaining = (this.totalCount * this.itemHeight) - this.scrollTop - this.containerHeight;
        return remaining < this.containerHeight * 2;
    }

    getVisibleRange() {
        const startIndex = Math.max(0, 
            Math.floor(this.scrollTop / this.itemHeight) - this.overscan
        );
        const endIndex = Math.min(this.totalCount,
            Math.ceil((this.scrollTop + this.containerHeight) / this.itemHeight) + this.overscan
        );
        return { startIndex, endIndex };
    }

    render() {
        const { startIndex, endIndex } = this.getVisibleRange();
        const visible = new Set();

        // Add/update visible items
        for (let i = startIndex; i < endIndex; i++) {
            visible.add(i);

            if (!this.items.has(i)) {
                const element = this.renderItem(i);
                element.style.position = "absolute";
                element.style.top = `${i * this.itemHeight}px`;
                element.style.left = "0";
                element.style.right = "0";
                element.dataset.index = i;

                this.inner.appendChild(element);
                this.items.set(i, element);
            }
        }

        // Remove items no longer visible
        for (const [index, element] of this.items) {
            if (!visible.has(index)) {
                element.remove();
                this.items.delete(index);
            }
        }

        console.debug(`[VirtualList] Rendering ${this.items.size} of ${this.totalCount} items`);
    }

    updateTotalCount(newCount) {
        this.totalCount = newCount;
        this.inner.style.height = `${newCount * this.itemHeight}px`;
        this.render();
    }

    scrollToIndex(index) {
        this.container.scrollTop = index * this.itemHeight;
    }

    destroy() {
        this.resizeObserver.disconnect();
        this.inner.remove();
    }
}
```

